AD | 4 min watch: A quick makeup look with some of my favourite @lancomeofficial products and some tips I’ve picked up along the way.

Prepping with the Advanced Génifique serum, one of my favourite anti aging serums - and perfect as a makeup base as well. 

The Teint Idôle Ultra Wear foundation is a classic for a reason - the ultimate matte - radiant hybrid. 

The Grandiose Liner has the perfect tip for precise application, while the Hypnôse Doll Eyes Mascara is super lengthening.

A subtle, subtle blush - the Blush Subtil in shade 351

Finishing off with the gorgeous La Vie Est Belle perfume. Always apply directly on skin!

All products available exclusively at @sephora_india - use my code KOMAL10 for deals on your purchase ✨

https://bit.ly/3yvZ4uH

#LuxeWithLancome #Lancome #LancomePartner #SayYesToHappiness

Beauty products as empty as my soul ahaha sorry 😁 One thing that always cheers me up is talking about skincare - here are all the products I used up until the very last drop over the last month!

@sundayriley @lorealindia @kerastase_official @elemis_india

Loving these two new launches from @pahadilocal, a brand which I am always so happy to talk about because their products are always so consistently great. There’s a Green Tea Face and Body Scrub which I like to double up as a mask as well, and a gorgeous Kishtwar Saffron Mist which is a lovely addition to any skincare routine. 

I’m not a huge fan of physical exfoliants but when it’s as gentle as the Green Tea scrub (it’s made of ground up leaves and nothing else), it can be a nice way to temporarily brighten your skin - but the green tea makes it so soothing. I used it as a mask to help with a sunburn on my back after the Andamans (the ONE day I forgot to reapply on my back) and it instantly calmed down the redness. 

And the saffron mist is just 🧡

Have you used either? Let me know!

An ad for @pahadilocal.

The @lancomeofficial Advanced Génifique serum was game-changing when it launched years ago and remains so with the addition of pre- and probiotics to strengthen the skin’s barrier. It’s one of the few products I always finish; I’ve introduced it to my mum who now loves it and it’s a lovely addition to any skincare routine. 
 
Lancôme is also hosting a giveaway of the Génifique serum – to enter, please follow them at @lancomeofficial and leave a comment below tagging 3 of your favourite friends. There’s one 30 ml bottle up for grabs along with nine 7 ml samples for 10 winners in total.
 
You can also get the Génifique at Sephora, or get a 7ml sample complimentary on purchases of over 4,000. The link is here: https://bit.ly/3I4qDNt
 
An AD for @lancomeofficial. #MySkinMyStrength #frenchluxurybeauty

These Garnier Micellar Pads might be the softest reusable rounds I’ve ever used. They are kitten soft. Bunny soft! Baby’s bottom soft? They’re very soft, which is nice because I am a capitalist wench who likes to have a little bit of luxury in every aspect of her life and these pads deliver that while also being eco-friendly. I feel a little bit of my soul die every time I use cotton rounds to remove sunscreen or makeup because I know reusable rounds abound, but they never feel as nice 😬 These ones do, and they clean up real well with a bit of soap and water, and they’re meant to last about a 1,000 washes. You get 3 in a box which makes it 3,000 washes; about 2,000 when you consider that like me, you will likely end up losing one in your sock drawer – but it’s still way better for the environment than my current Bella cotton rounds and they feel way more luxurious than their price would suggest, so it’s a win on all counts for me. Have you tried them? You get them at Amazon and at Nykaa.

I found a brand called @foxtaleskin on Instagram about a month ago which looked an awful lot like @drunkelephant and ordered some of their products because don’t knock it until you’ve tried it even if they display zero creativity spine or integrity? I’ve been using the products for a month, here are some thoughts. 🍊 

What do you think? Does the similarity intrigue you enough to give them a try? I’d love to know your thoughts!

Here’s one way I know the last two years have been a blur - I keep saying this video is of my 2020 favourites when I really mean 2021. Also I know we’re well into 2022 but it’s taken me a while to sit down and film this - January’s been a long year. What even is time any more? Anyway! These are some of my favourite products which I either discovered or used for the first time in 2021. Not 2020! ✨

French luxury beauty brand @lancomeofficial is back in India exclusively at @sephora_india, both online and in stores and the excitement is very real. Here’s what I’ve used in this video – The Advanced Genefique Youth Activating Serum, which is so super for strengthening the skin barrier, the Teint Idole Ultra Wear Foundation, L’Absolu Rouge Drama Matte Lip Stick in Sensualite, the Grandiose Liner and La Vie Est Belle Parfum. Shop them all at https://sephora.nnow.com/lancome. 

Happy, happy New Year peeps! 

And #AD for @lancomeofficial. 

#Lancome #Genefique #MySkinMyStrength #TeintIdoleUltraWear #frenchluxurybeauty

A super quick review of Fresh Affair, the new dry shampoo from @kerastase_official. It’s light, it isn’t chalky, it doesn’t leave a gritty residue and it makes your hair smell like you’ve just washed it even when you er, haven’t. This is important, because most dry shampoos, even my favourites, are designed to hit you over the head with their fragrance. Not the case with this one. I love working with Kerastase because their products are so freaking fantastic – this one is a perfect example. Are you a fan of dry shampoo? Think your’ll try this one? Let me know if you have any questions at all! 

An #AD for @kerastase_official.

Merry Christmas Eve and it’s giveaway time! I love the @kerastase_official Elixir Ultime, it’s likely my most used hair product. The serum is great for before or after a blow dry to make your hair so ridiculously soft and shiny and frizz-free. I wanted to set the rules for this giveaway, so here they are!

Follow @kerastase_official and then tell me something you LOVE about your hair. I know we’re all about trying to fix the things we don’t like when it comes to our hair but I’d like for us to think about something we like about it and say it without feeling like we’re boasting somehow, or being narcissistic.

It’s weird because I’m meant to go first and it feels really odd to say something positive about my hair because it feels so pompous somehow. I’d be way happier talking about how I’ve spent countless hours trying to make it something it’s not - wavy, voluminous, PURPLE. 😄 We’re conditioned to be more comfortable talking about the things we don’t like about our physical appearances than we are stating the things we do. Anyway. I like how shiny my hair is. I like how soft it feels after I run a brush through it, and I like how my hair has always felt like a big part of my identity. Writing this I realise that mostly, I’m just thankful for it, and for withstanding the abuse I’ve put it through over the years 😁

Now you go! 

An #AD for #KerastaseIndia 

#KerastaseClub #CraveTheIconic #ElixirUltime #ChristmasGiveaway

EDIT: Thanks so much for participating in the giveaway! The winners are @gislam1 and @vandita_agrawal! Please DM me with your address and contact details!

latestPosts.caption: This is what we’ve been up to over the last two days, and I am now up to my ears in all things Star Wars. Galaxy’s Edge at Disneyland is worth all the hype; so much so that @omerbasith teared up when we first walked in which was nice because it’s comforting to know that he does have feelings. In all seriousness though the rides are amazing, the experience is completely immersive and you feel like you’re in the Star Wars universe - if you’re a Star Wars fan go, go, go.

Hello from the very last row on this Emirates flight to Dubai and then on to San Francisco! I have had a lot of time to myself on this journey thanks to the magic of iPads and have spent the most part of it thinking, particularly of the many advantages life confers upon you once you decide to have children. Here they are in no particular order:

Children drain not just your energy, time and emotions, but also your money. This is a good thing because once you decide that you’d rather eat lauki for a month than fork over the cash for four business class tickets, life feels simpler, less complicated, and also very very cramped. This allows you to think upon the things that you take for granted in your everyday life like walking, kicking your legs about with free abandon (another underrated privilege) and also, couches. Couches are a good thing and we do not appreciate them enough. Have you ever stretched your legs out on your own couch, knowing that the chances of hitting the back of someone else’s as you do so are slim to none? If so then I say to you that you are a king and I won’t let anyone tell you otherwise. 

The other advantage of having children is that you can spend weeks planning the perfect trip to a Disneyland halfway across the globe only to be sitting next to your child on the flight there and have them point to the map and tell you it would’ve been easier to stop over in Japan instead, leading you to question not just your life choices but also exactly what it is they’re learning in school, and that is the kind of fun simply not afforded to those who use protection. 

Overall, this trip has been great so far and being on the last row means we may as well be invisible to the crew and so I’ve had the time of my life eavesdropping. There’s a 23-year-old who’s tired of working and wants to be married by 28, LATEST 29 - love is important but money is slightly more important - another is 32 and says he’s a grandpa and is ready to settle down (think he’s dropping hints) - and another has the best contact for an injector in Dubai. If she actually shares details I’ll let you know! And this is why it’s a bad idea to give people WiFi on flights.

I went to @lancomeofficial Open Lab in Mumbai the other day to meet with @drannieblack who is the chief formulator of product at Lancôme. She’s updated the iconic Lancôme Génifique and updated it to make it even more powerful with the addition of beta glucan to further strengthen the skin barrier in the new Lancôme Génifique Ultimate Serum with Beta Glucan. It’s an incredible formula that is somehow even more effective than its predecessor, which is no mean feat!

Disclaimer: I have personally used the product or service and the statements made in the ad are a reflection of my own experience. I have clearly mentioned the same in the advertisement and not tried to generalize the claim, as others’ experience could be different.

latestPosts.caption:
The week that was. A blur of noise and colour and chaos, sometimes overwhelming, often joyful. Went to watch Flow with the kids, both mine and my friends’ – it certainly feels more grown up than the 6+ rating would suggest! We have family staying with us; spent time with my nephew, went to breakfast at Brik Oven with @siddb17 and my sisters in law @asiya_ashraff and @samiasbarron_ , wrapped Eid presents and then did something just for myself – went to @kaash.space for a talk, but mainly to see @sridharpoddar and @deeptichandy. Every time I see them I come away feeling happier than I was before, and Kaash is such a gorgeous space with so many beautiful things to feast your eyes upon.
 
And now I’ve sent everyone off to have lunch without me so I can finally take the Christmas tree down (just in time for Eid lunch tomorrow! I was this close to just putting a star and a moon on the top and calling it an Eid tree), and finally sit down and enjoy this dishy, gossipy book about Cecil Beaton’s life. I hope you’re having a lovely weekend! ♥️

latestPosts.caption: I’ve been really into solid perfume recently - they’re not as overpowering as regular fragrances, they last longer, and they’re easy to travel with so you can reapply through the day without knocking everyone out with a cloud of fragrance. I’ve been really liking these three - have you tried any of them? @thejoonshop @diptyque

I really do appreciate a brand that delivers considered launches, prioritising effectiveness and addressing actual pain points over just rushing to bring a product to market. Take an exfoliant for sensitive skin, for example - it’s best to tread lightly and I find brands don’t often get that right - not the case with Clinique’s Moisture Surge Active Glow Serum. If you’re familiar with the Moisture Surge moisturiser, you’ll know what I mean when I say that the serum is similarly fuss free yet effective without irritating skin. It features lactic acid for gentle exfoliation, hyaluronic acid for added hydration and Vitamin C, but it doesn’t sting even sensitised skin like mine. This isn’t the serum for magical, overnight results (but then again, very few are) - instead, this delivers gentle exfoliation and brightening over time. I’ve noticed plumper skin - foundation goes on so much more smoothly - reduced redness and brighter, more even skin. Another win from @clinique_in! 

#CliniqueIndia #CrackTheGlowCode #ActivateYourGlow

I really don’t know if this whole video is a nothing burger and I’m just saying stuff that everyone already knows but this is a reminder that you’re not what you look like on camera - figuratively, but also literally 💙
